underlying_goal: Analyze experiment outputs to understand the performance of the C³ detection method on the USACO dataset, find the worst-performing prompts, and identify any conflicting or anomalous results.
primary_success: Successfully identified and synthesized findings from multiple conflicting result files, uncovering a critical insight that the detection method's failure on USACO was fundamental and that initial positive results were due to small sample sizes or data labeling errors.
brief_summary: User requested analysis of USACO C³ experiment results. Claude conducted a deep dive into output files, uncovering three conflicting sets of results. It correctly diagnosed them as original (failed), inverted (label error), and corrected (strong performance), and synthesized findings from other analysis documents to conclude that the method was fundamentally flawed for this dataset due to small-sample optimism.
